{
  "texts": [
    "Challenges related to bias, misinformation, and data quality have been addressed through comprehensive verification frameworks, incorporating both automated algorithms and human oversight [67,68,69,70,71].",
    "The ongoing development of more sophisticated verification and validation methodologies will be critical for the future of trustworthy and reliable AI applications [57,59,72,67].Algorithm 1 Dynamic Linking for GPT-Neo Q ← new query from GPT-Neo S ← set of data sources R ← ∅ (initialize relevant data set) for s ∈ S do D s ← fetch data from s I s ← index(D s, criteria = {relevance, recency, reliability}) for d ∈ D s do if isRelevant(d, Q) ∧ isRecent(d) ∧ isReliable(d) then R ← R ∪ {d} end ifend for end for Transform(R) to match GPT-Neo's internal data format return R as enriched data for GPT-Neo Proposed MethodThis paper introduces a novel approach for incremental knowledge enrichment tailored to the GPT-Neo architecture, aiming to bridge the gap between the model's static knowledge base and the dynamic nature of real-world information.",
    "Our methodology is grounded in a theoretical framework that emphasizes the seamless integration of new information, ensuring the model remains current and accurate.",
    "We propose a dual-phase process that involves the dynamic linking of external data sources with the internal knowledge representation of GPT-Neo and the rigorous verification of this information to maintain the integrity and trustworthiness of the model.",
    "Dynamic Linking MechanismThe dynamic linking mechanism forms the foundation of our proposed method, enabling GPT-Neo to integrate real-time information from diverse external data sources."
  ]
}